v. Nor crush e worm, whose useful light Might serve, however small, To show e stumbling-stone by night, And save him from afell. vi. Whate'er she meent, this truth divine Is legible and plain, 'Tis power almighty bids him shine, Nor bids him shine in vein. vn. Ye proud and wealthy, let this theme Teaeh humbler thoughts to you, Since such a reptile has its gem,

And boasts its splendour too.
